title: Pa. Girls: Pa. girls: Abington hands Upper Dublin first loss
text:
Sun Valley 4, Interboro 1: Samantha Bowen had a goal and an assist for the visitors. Ashley Hoy, Elizabeth Morgan, and Julia Skwirut also scored.
BICENTENNIAL LEAGUE 
New Hope-Solebury 2, Calvary Christian 0: Lea Brussock and Claudia Kolinak each scored goals on the road. 
PIONEER ATHLETIC CONFERENCE 
Phoenixville 1, Upper Perkiomen 0: Leeza Galli scored the lone goal for the hosts on an assist from Kaitlyn Casiano. 
Spring-Ford 2, Methacton 0: Molly McHarg and Laura Suero each scored goals at home. 
PUBLIC LEAGUE 
Masterman 2, Philadelphia Academy Charter 1: Olive Garst and Ruby Johnston scored second half-goals in the comeback win on the road. 
Prep Charter 5, Science Leadership Academy 1: Makhira Brown and Courtney Harold each scored two goals at home. Torri Burrell also scored. FIELD HOCKEY 
BICENTENNIAL LEAGUE 
Christopher Dock 2, Lower Moreland 1: Macy Balmer and Jill Bolton each scored second-half goals for the visitors. 
SUBURBAN ONE CONTINENTAL 
Souderton 3, Central Bucks East 2: Nina Disco had a goal and an assist on the road. Rachel Kagarise and Erin Saybolt also scored. 
CATHOLIC ACADEMIES 
Villa Maria 3, Merion Mercy 2: Megan Vermeil scored two goals, and Abby Siana added another for the home side. 
NONLEAGUE 
Interboro 2, Penncrest 1: Steph McCool and Ro Murphy each scored for the home team, and Jess Hinchey made six saves. 
George School 1, Morrisville 0: Selah Kamau scored four minutes into the second half on the road. VOLLEYBALL 
SUBURBAN ONE NATIONAL 
Council Rock North 3, Neshaminy 0: Hadley Grundman had six kills and two aces at home. Danae Barkley added seven kills.
